
- Implement R level Gaussian code


  

################################################################################
Expected user-inputs
################################################################################
Binomial data
# Inputs
  o Y nxJ matrix of counts (or 0s and 1s)
  o Ntrials nxJ matrix of number of trials (1 for binary data)
  o X list of length J with each list entry an nxp_j matrix
  o offset matrix of offsets into the linear predictor
  o A nxn binary adjacency matrix
  o attractive number of attractive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o repulsive number of repulsive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o tol tolerance for MCSE
  o minit min MCMC sample sze
  o maxit max MCMC sample size
# Initial values
  - beta, Psi, Sigma
# Hyperparameters
  - taub: precision of beta
  - a.s and b.s: shape and scale for Sigma
# Tuning parameters (tune Metropolis acceptance)
  - sigmab Jx1 vector for regression coefficients
  - sigmas Jx1 vector for spatial effects

  
Poisson data
# Inputs
  o Y nxJ matrix of counts
  o X list of length J with each list entry an nxp_j matrix
  o offset matrix of offsets into the linear predictor
  o A nxn binary adjacency matrix
  o attractive number of attractive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o repulsive number of repulsive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o tol tolerance for MCSE
  o minit min MCMC sample sze
  o maxit max MCMC sample size
# Initial values
  o beta list of p_jx1 vectors, j=1,...,J
  o Psi list of J qx1 vectors
  o Sigma JxJ matrix
  o hetero (optional) list of J qx1 vectors
# Hyperparameters
  o taub: precision of beta
  o a.s and b.s: shape and scale for Sigma
  o tauh: precision of hetero (if desired)
# Tuning parameters (tune Metropolis acceptance)
  o sigmab Jx1 vector for regression coefficients
  o sigmas Jx1 vector for spatial effects
  o sigmah: Jx1 vector for hetero random effects
  

Gaussian data
# Inputs
  o Y nxJ matrix of continuous values
  o X list of length J with each list entry an nxp_j matrix
  o A nxn binary adjacency matrix
  o attractive number of attractive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o repulsive number of repulsive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o tol tolerance for MCSE
  o minit min MCMC sample sze
  o maxit max MCMC sample size
# Initial values
  o beta list of p_jx1 vectors, j=1,...,J
  o Psi list of J qx1 vectors
  o Sigma JxJ matrix
# Hyperparameters
  o taub: precision of beta
  o a.s and b.s: shape and scale for Sigma
  o tauh: precision of hetero (i.e., Gaussian variance at likelihood level)
    - a.h and b.h: shape and scale for hetero
# Tuning parameters (tune Metropolis acceptance)
  o sigmab Jx1 vector for regression coefficients
  o sigmas Jx1 vector for spatial effects
  
  
Zero-inflated data
# Inputs
  o Y nx1 vector of counts
  o X list of length 2 with each list entry an nxp_j matrix
  o offset matrix of offsets into the linear predictor for count part
  o A nxn binary adjacency matrix
  o attractive number of attractive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o repulsive number of repulsive Moran eigenvectors to use
  o tol tolerance for MCSE
  o minit min MCMC sample sze
  o maxit max MCMC sample size
# Initial values
  o beta list of p_jx1 vectors, j=1,2
  o Psi list of 2 qx1 vectors
  o Sigma 2x2 matrix
  o hetero (optional) list of qx1 vectors for count model
# Hyperparameters
  o taub: precision of beta
  o a.s and b.s: shape and scale for Sigma
  o tauh: precision of hetero (if desired)
# Tuning parameters (tune Metropolis acceptance)
  o sigmab: 2x1 vector for regression coefficients
  o sigmas: 2x1 vector for spatial effects
  o sigmah: vector for hetero random effects